# Leftovers.
Did you know America watses between 30%-40% of its food supply ever year? A large part of this waste is on the consumer side. Consumers in the US throw away over one hundred million pounds of food every year. With the food crisis the world is in right now, we can't afford this time of loss. That's why we built Leftovers.
# We're here to change that
Leftovers is an app that ensures people don't throw away leftovers that they forgot were in the fridge. We do this by sending text notifications during peak meal times. These texts remind you about your leftovers and estimate how long it is until they expire. Hopefully, we can raise the percentage of people that actually eat their leftovers to above 20.
